skiaui provides CMake targets:

  find_package(SkiaUI CONFIG REQUIRED)
  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE SkiaUI::Skui)

The optional Win32 platform adapter is available with:

  vcpkg install skiaui[win32]

Then link:

  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE SkiaUI::SkuiWin32)

The optional Win32/DX12 host is available with:

  vcpkg install skiaui[win32-dx12]

Then link:

  target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE SkiaUI::SkuiWin32Dx12)

SkiaUI depends on the target project's Skia build. If your project uses a
different rendering backend, depend on Skia features that match that backend
and embed SkiaUI through SkiaUI::Skui. Windows OpenGL/Vulkan hosts can reuse
SkiaUI::SkuiWin32 for Win32 input, clipboard, IME, and cursor handling without
linking the DX12 host.

The optional SkiaUiDesk demo executable is available with:

  vcpkg install skiaui[demo]

After installation, run:

  <vcpkg-root>\installed\<triplet>\tools\skiaui\SkiaUiDesk.exe
